</P>
<P>
   G7-MEETING (Washington) _ Developments from the meeting of the
top economic officials of the world's wealthiest nations. By David
E. Sanger.
</P>
<P>
   TAIWAN-AFTERSHOCK (Tokyo) _ Taiwan suffers a massive aftershock
that killed at least three people and injured 58 others, destroyed
buildings and roads already weakened from Tuesday's devastating
earthquake, and sent thousands of horrified residents scurrying for
cover. By Calvin Sims.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-YELTSIN (Moscow) _ President Boris Yelstin's wife goes on
television to defend her family against corruption charges. By
Michael R. Gordon.
</P>
