against militants in Chechnya and Dagestan. By Michael R. Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   TIMOR-ALBRIGHT (Undated) _ Secretary of State Madeleine Albright
meets with the leader of East Timor's independence movement. By
Barbara Crossette.
</P>
<P>
   PINOCHET (London) _ Gen. Augusto Pinochet, the former Chilean
dictator who has called himself ``the only political prisoner in
England'' since his arrest here nearly a year ago, begins finding
out this week whether he must go to Spain to face charges of crimes
against humanity. By Warren Hoge.
</P>
