<P>
   &QL; 
SALVAGE _ The almost-new, shiny-white Jeep Cherokee looked awfully
sweet when Warren Hill paid $23,024 for it at a Fresno, Calif.,
auto dealership in 1993. But when he tried to trade it two years
later, Hill said records revealed the car had been in a terrible
collision and was ``structurally unsound.'' Hill's case is among
those being cited by ``lemon'' purchasers and consumer groups
wondering why Congress can't seem to pass a tough bill to prevent
the sale of rebuilt wrecks. By JEFF BARKER. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
QUAYLE _ Former Vice President Dan Quayle ended his long-shot bid
for the White House on Sunday, hobbled by his inability to raise
enough money to compete against the juggernaut of front-runner,
George W. Bush. The decision came just as Quayle, was made after
Quayle determined that even a good finish in New Hampshire's early
primary and moderate success in fund-raising would be insufficient
to beat out Bush. By KRIS MAYES. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL;
